[Area of a Regular Polygon]
Equivalent to half of the product of a polygon's apothem length and its
perimeter.
A = 1/2ap.

––––––––––––-––––––––––––-––––––––––––-––––––––––––-––––––––––––-––––––––––––-–

What is the area of a regular octagon that as a side length of 10mm and is 13mm
from the center to a vertex?

Perimeter.................
p = nl
p = 8 * 10
p = 80

a.........................
a^2 + b^2 = c^2
a^2 + (10/2)^2 = 13^2
a^2 + 5^2 = 13^2
a^2 + 25 = 169
a^2 = 144
a = sqrt(144)
a = 12

A.........................
A = 1/2ap
A = 1/2(12)(80)
A = 480

