What is the area of a regular octagon with a side length of 4.6 meters and a
length from the center to a vertex of 6 meters?

Perimeter..................
p = nl
p = 4.6 * 8
p = 36.8

Apothem....................
a^2 + b^2 = c^2
a^2 + 2.3^2 = 6^2
a^2 + 5.29 = 36
a^2 = 30.71
a = sqrt(30.71)

Area.......................
A = 1/2ap
A = 1/2(sqrt(30.71))(36.8)
A = 18.4 * sqrt(30.71)

