What is the area of a regular hexagon with a side length of 5.2 centimeters and
a distance from the center to a vertex of 5.2 centimeters?

Perimeter...................
p = nl
p = 6 * 5.2
p = 31.2

Apothem.....................
a^2 + b^2 = c^2
a^2 + (5.2/2)^2 = 5.2^2
a^2 + 2.6^2 = 5.2^2
a^2 + 6.76 = 27.04
a^2 = 20.28
a = sqrt(20.28)

Area........................
A = 1/2ap
A = 1/2(sqrt(20.28))(31.2)
A = 15.6 * sqrt(20.28)

