What is the area of a regular pentagon with a side length of 7 feet and a
length from the center to a vertex of 6 feet?

Perimeter.................
p = nl
p = 5 * 7
p = 35

Apothem...................
a^2 + b^2 = c^2
a^2 + (7/2)^2 = 6^2
a^2 + 3.5^2 = 6^2
a^2 + 12.25 = 36
a^2 = 23.75
a = sqrt(23.75)

Area......................
A = 1/2ap
A = 1/2(sqrt(23.75))(35)
A = 17.5 * sqrt(23.75)

